<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="321" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1081,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,277,1081,1106]" pageId="16" pageNumber="321">Discussion</emphasis>
. The species is easy to identify by 
<number box="[675,689,1081,1105]" pageId="16" pageNumber="321" value="5.0">5</number>
black ocelli and short chaetae on body. A form with unpigmented ommatidia often occurs among normal specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="321" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1081,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,493,1153,1178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="321">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
. The species is distributed in arid areas of S Siberia (Khakassia, Altai, Tuva, Chita area). It was recorded in Burytia by 
<bibRefCitation box="[571,841,1189,1213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="321" refString="Chimitova, A. B., Chernova, N. M. &amp; Potapov. M. B. (2010) Springtail (Collembola) populations in cryogenic soils of the Vitim Plateau. Entomological Review, 90, 957 - 967. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0013873810080014" type="journal article">
Chimitova 
<emphasis box="[699,750,1189,1213]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="321">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[774,833,1189,1213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="321" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation box="[858,929,1189,1213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1885,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,700,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,700,1864]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. The sampling sites in Buryatia: 1 – 2 — Vitim Plateau (1 — Konda Basin, 2 — Eravna Basin), 3 – 5 — Selenga Low Plateau (3 — Zagansky Range, 4 — vicinities of Schuch'ye Lake, 5 — vicinities of Karasinoye Lake), 6 – 8 — Barguzinsky Range (6 — Ust' - Barguzin, 7 — vicinities of Barguzin, 8 — upper flow of Barguzin River), 9 — Khamar-Daban Range, 10 — Tunkinskiye Gol'tsy Range, 11 — vicinities of Ulan-Ude, 12 — estuary of Selenga River, 13 — vicinities of Khorinsk, 14 — vicinities of Unnokent'evka, 15 –– Turka." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254496/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="321">
Fig. 
<number box="[913,929,1189,1213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="321" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
: loc. 
<number box="[994,1011,1189,1213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="321" value="2.0">2</number>
). Only in steppes, penetrates to salty places, very rare in dry forests.
</paragraph>
